<Author>jamaicabound3
<Content>Wonderful stay will be back My husband, mother-in-law and I recently stayed at Palmas de Lucia. The check in staff was very friendly we had a wait because the people in front of us had not booked and paid online but when I told the front desk staff we needed to rush because we were closing on a house they expedited our check in. The food was great my mother-in-law hates to eat out but she LOVED the food there. She said the red snapper was the best she had ever eaten! I am vegetarian and they had no problems accommodating my diet (the marinara sauce was excellent). Ozmin and Ramon were excellent waiters!!! The rooms were clean a few ants were seen at times but nothing to complain about. All rooms have a TV and a refrigerator. The pool was very clean. Also being in the health profession I found it very impressive the hotel has an AED!!The beach is down the road it has sea grass and not maintained by the hotel. The water was rough while we were there but it was still beautiful to look at. Great place to relax and reflect.The only complaint we had was the bar down the road plays the music REALLY loud on the weekend (it is against the law to play music during the week). (They do make great drinks.) My husband and I just drowned the music out with the TV but my mother-in-law had a rough time with the loud music. Next time we will request rooms down the hall. If you are looking for a 5 star hotel this hotel is not for you! If you are looking for off the beaten path were you can spend time with native Puerto Ricans, and enjoy the ocean then this is the place for you. It is best to rent a car to travel to the Bacardi tour, to the rainforest and/or any other great spots in PR . Before you go on an excursion stop by the stores along the road by the hotel. They do speak English and carry ice chests, ice, drinks, snacks, etc. The Puerto Rican people at the stores were very welcoming.We chose this hotel because we were in Puerto Rico to purchase a house. We wanted to save money but also wanted to be close to our house ; the Palmas de Lucia was the PERFECT spot. Since the Palmas is close to our new house if our house is not finished when we return to PR we will definitely stay at the Palmas de Lucia if our house is fixed we will definitely be back for meals and to visit the GREAT STAFF. 
<Date>Apr 12, 2008
