<Author>JJ_Adventures
<Content>Terrible Parador Experience DO NOT GO HERE. You will be disappointed.  I have heard great things about other Paradores, but this one is an exception. They have a nice website on which they advertise their proximity to the beach and exquisite restaurant menu, among other things.  The public beach next to the property is 100 feet away as advertised, but they left out the fact that is full of garbage and inhabited by stray dogs (one of which I saw lying dead in the surf, and it looked like it had been there a while). I have never been so disgusted by a beach before in my life; not what one looks for on vacation. The restaurant was a similarly terrible experience. The service was slow and confused, and the food was even worse. $15+ USD for reheated steak and frozen vegetables. Enough said. In all fairness the room was clean and comfortable, but considering the other factors, not at all worth what they charge.  I would not even recommend visiting this area of the island. All of the beaches seemed to be severely neglected and there is an oil refinery 10 minutes up the highway. 
