<Author>pch71
<Content>My honest opinion... We stayed at Palmas de Lucia on the weekend of Sept 29th-Oct 1st. I have to say that I have mixed feelings about this place. Check in was quick and the lady at the front desk was very nice. Small pool, but my nieces and nephews did not seem to mind, they had a great time at the pool. The area around the pool was nice, but outside the hotel is kind of dirty and the beach is no a good one for swimming. I found a broken beer bottle on the sand. The rooms were ok, nothing fancy, with a little fridge and microwave, and the beds were comfortable. But it was very humid inside the room! The bathroom was another story. Very bad design, and no air vents. Had a hard time to get warm water, it was like extremely cold or extremely hot. After a while trying, we got warm water. The outlet was broken, so I could not plug my hair dryer. Apparently this is an ongoing problem, since another room in our party had the same problem. And the room smelled musty. The room had a balcony looking to the pool. My husband and father in law had breakfast at the restaurant, and they were not happy. They said it was not good at all. We went on sunday to a nearby bakery and bought bread, ham and cheese and had breakfast. We did not use the restaurant for dinner, since we were there for a wedding in nearby Humacao, so we ate there, and I'm glad it was that way. Also the room doors and the frame are metal, so every time you close the door, it slams. Slams so hard that I could hear it from far away. A little annoying. I'm not a picky person, the only thing I ask for is a room in working order.I do not think I will stay again.... 
