<Content>Charming Paradores I have fond memories of this area from visiting Yabucoa as a child. I stayed here in April of 2004 with my 6 yr old son at Palmas de Lucia for 8 nights and enjoyed the facilities, warm and welcoming staff, and cleanliness of the rooms. All of the staff was bi-lingual which very helpful. My son enjoyed the game room, basketball court and pool. This truly could be considered a family resort. The beach adjacent to this property should be for walking and sunbathing only as the currents and riptides are dangerous, it is nonetheless very picturesque, soothing and a relaxing place to vist. The only recommendation or drawback when traveling with children here is that the menu for the restaurant is somewhat limited for a childrens menu. If you have a rental car there are supermarkets and other Americanized restaurants close by to get you over that challenge! This was a memorable trip for my son and myself! 
